T2  - Journal of Political Economy
JF  - Journal of Political Economy
SP  - 816
EP  - 819
VL  - 90
IS  - 4
PB  - The University of Chicago Press
N2  - Why should a rationally motivated political decision process generate an inverse relationship between tax rates and tax revenues? There would never seem a logical reason for increasing tax rates beyond maximum revenue limits. In this note, we explain how such a position can emerge and show why, once in such a position, political decision makers may find it difficult to escape.
AB  - Why should a rationally motivated political decision process generate an inverse relationship between tax rates and tax revenues? There would never seem a logical reason for increasing tax rates beyond maximum revenue limits. In this note, we explain how such a position can emerge and show why, once in such a position, political decision makers may find it difficult to escape.
SN  - 0022-3808
M3  - doi: 10.1086/261091
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1086/261091
Y2  - 2024/03/22
